{"type": "standard", "title": "Krill", "displaytitle": "<span lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Krill</span></span>", "namespace": {"id": 0, "text": ""}, "wikibase_item": "Q29498", "titles": {"canonical": "Krill", "normalized": "Krill", "display": "<span lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Krill</span></span>"}, "pageid": 231145, "thumbnail": {"source": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Meganyctiphanes_norvegica2.jpg/330px-Meganyctiphanes_norvegica2.jpg", "width": 330, "height": 189}, "originalimage": {"source": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e3/Meganyctiphanes_norvegica2.jpg", "width": 1750, "height": 1000}, "lang": "en", "dir": "ltr", "revision": "1358153655", "tid": "df397ee6-61fa-11f1-aafd-58e655ee3e2f", "timestamp": "2026-06-06T22:55:54Z", "description": "Small, shrimp-like crustaceans; order of crustaceans", "description_source": "local", "content_urls": {"desktop": {"page": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krill", "revisions": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krill?action=history", "edit": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krill?action=edit", "talk": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Krill"}, "mobile": {"page": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krill", "revisions": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:History/Krill", "edit": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krill?action=edit", "talk": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Talk:Krill"}}, "extract": "Krill (Euphausiids) are small and exclusively marine crustaceans of the order Euphausiacea, found in all of the world's oceans. The name \"krill\" comes from the Norwegian word krill, meaning \"small fry of fish\", which is also often attributed to species of fish.", "extract_html": "<p><b>Krill</b> <i>(Euphausiids)</i> are small and exclusively marine crustaceans of the order <b>Euphausiacea</b>, found in all of the world's oceans. The name \"krill\" comes from the Norwegian word <i><span><i lang=\"no\"><span class=\"extiw\">krill</span></i></span></i>, meaning \"small fry of fish\", which is also often attributed to species of fish.</p>"}